titleStmt.title: Anno primo Reginæ Elizabethe At the parliament begonne at Westmynster, the xxiii. of January in the fyrste yeare of the reigne of oure Soueraigne Ladye, Elizabeth by the grace of God, of England, Fraunce and Ireland, Quene, defendoure of the faithe, [et]c. And there proroged tyll the. xxv. of the same moneth, and then and there holden, kept, and continued vntill the dissolution of the same, beyng the eyght day of May, then nexte ensuynge, were enacted as foloweth.
Public General Acts. 1559-1560. 1 Elizabeth I

notesStmt.note: Running title reads: Anno primo Reginæ Elizabethe.
In this edition, line 6 of title has: January; 1st line of table: 'act restoring'.
At least parts of quires A, D-F are by a different printer or compositor, who uses some Whitchurch/Grafton initials and a few criblé initials belonging to J. Kingston--STC.
Reproduction of original in the Lincoln's Inn Library, London, England.
